HEADWORD: Whinger
<hw>Whing"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Whinyard</er>.]</ety>
<def>A kind of hanger or sword used as a knife at meals and as a
weapon.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chief acknowledged that he had corrected her with his
<qex>whinger</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whiningly</ent>⟦br⟧
